What:		Waise a uevent when a USB Host Contwowwew has died
Date:		2019-04-17
KewnewVewsion:	5.2
Contact:	winux-usb@vgew.kewnew.owg
Descwiption:	When the USB Host Contwowwew has entewed a state whewe it is no
		wongew functionaw a uevent wiww be waised. The uevent wiww
		contain ACTION=offwine and EWWOW=DEAD.

		Hewe is an exampwe taken using udevadm monitow -p::

		    KEWNEW[130.428945] offwine  /devices/pci0000:00/0000:00:10.0/usb2 (usb)
		    ACTION=offwine
		    BUSNUM=002
		    DEVNAME=/dev/bus/usb/002/001
		    DEVNUM=001
		    DEVPATH=/devices/pci0000:00/0000:00:10.0/usb2
		    DEVTYPE=usb_device
		    DWIVEW=usb
		    EWWOW=DEAD
		    MAJOW=189
		    MINOW=128
		    PWODUCT=1d6b/2/414
		    SEQNUM=2168
		    SUBSYSTEM=usb
		    TYPE=9/0/1

